snippet.title: Sean Evans Learns How to Make Sushi | Sean in the Wild
snippet.description:
Culinary neophyte Sean Evans has learned how to scramble an egg and sear a steak, but now he's up against his toughest challenge yet. Does he have what it takes to make it as a sushi chef? In the hopes of learning this highly skilled trade, Sean enrolls at the Sushi Chef Instituteâ€”an intensive, two-month course led by chef Andy Matsuda. From scaling a fish to molding nigiri, Sean learns the sushi-making basics from a real master. Will Sean make the grade or flunk his midterm? Find out on an all new episode of Sean in the Wild.
